subject: Baseball
lead_paragraph: Yankees shortstop Derek Jeter had four hits for the first time since August 2012, a day after catcher Brian McCann predicted as much, while Masahiro Tanaka bounced back from his first loss in a 7-1 road win over the White Sox.
